<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>SAMS | Students Attendance Management System</title>
  <script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/f6549854b5.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/main.css">
  <link rel="icon" type="image/x-icon" href="/images/logo.ico">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/stylesheets/home.css">
</head>

<body>
  <!-- HEADER -->
  <header class="header">
    <div class="logo">
      <img src="/images/logo.jpg" draggable="false">
      <h2><span>Students Attendance Management System - </span>SAMS</h2>
    </div>
    <nav class="navbar">
      <a href="adminlogin">Admin<i class="fa-solid fa-user-shield"></i></a>
    </nav>
  </header>
  <!-- HEADER -->

  <!-- HOME -->
  <section class="home" id="home">
    <div class="home-container">

      <div class="left">
        <h1 class="left-title">Welcome to the<br>SAMS Community</h1>
        <p class="left-para">SAMS is a learning platform designed to provide educators, administrators and learners with
          a
          single robust, secure and integrated system to create personalised learning environments.</p>
        <button class="btn" onclick="moveCursor()">Let's Get Started<i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></button>
      </div>

      <div class="right">
        <div class="login-box">
          <div class="login-option">
            <button class="btn2 active" id="student-login-btn">Student Login</button>
            <button class="btn2" id="teacher-login-btn">Teacher Login</button>
          </div>
          <div class="student-login-form" id="student-login-form">
            <form action="studentlogin" method="POST">
              <% if (message) { %>
                <div class="alert show">
                  <span class="fa-solid fa-circle-exclamation"></span>
                  <span class="msg">Warning: <%= message %></span>
                  <span class="close-btn">
                    <span class="fa-solid fa-times"></span>
                  </span>
                </div>
              <% } %>
              <% if (message2){ %>
                <div class="alert show success">
                  <span class="fa-solid fa-circle-check"></span>
                  <span class="msg">Success: <%= message2 %></span>
                  <span class="close-btn" >
                    <span class="fa-solid fa-times"></span>
                  </span>
                </div>
              <% } %>
              <label for="student_email">Email or username</label>
              <input type="email" id="student-email" name="student_email" required>
              <label for="student_pass">Password</label>
              <input type="password" id="student-pass" name="student_pass" required>
              <button type="submit" class="btn login-btn">Login</button>
            </form>
            <p class="regp">Not registered yet? <a href="studentregister">Register now</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="teacher-login-form" id="teacher-login-form">
            <form action="teacherlogin" method="POST">
              <label for="teacher_email">Email or username</label>
              <input type="email" id="teacher-email" name="teacher_email">
              <label for="teacher_pass">Password</label>
              <input type="password" id="teacher-pass" name="teacher_pass">
              <button type="submit" class="btn login-btn">Login</button>
            </form>
            <p class="regp">Not registered yet? <a href="teacherregister">Register now</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <!-- HOME -->

  <!-- ABOUT -->

  <section class="about" id="about">
    <div class="about-container">
      <h1 class="about-heading">ABOUT US
        <hr>
        <hr>
      </h1>
      <p class="about-para">The easy to use online student attendance system make taking attendance quick and less prone
        to errors. Record a student’s attendance on the colored chart with a click of the mouse. The information
        pertaining to the student attendance can then be immediately shared with database to help the institutions keep
        track of their students via our student attendance management system.</p>
      <h3 class="about-title">All-in-one learning platform</h3>
      <p class="about-desc">SAMS provides the most flexible tool-set to support both blended learning and 100% digital
        attendance system.</p>
      <h3 class="about-title">Easy to use</h3>
      <p class="about-desc">A simple interface and well-documented resources along with ongoing usability improvements
        make SAMS easy to learn and use</p>
      <h3 class="about-title">Always up-to-date.</h3>
      <p class="about-desc">The SAMS project’s open-source approach means that SAMS is continually being reviewed and
        improved on to suit the current and evolving needs of its users.</p>
      <h3 class="about-title">Use any time, anywhere, on any device</h3>
      <p class="about-desc">SAMS is web-based and so can be accessed from anywhere in the world. With a default
        mobile-compatible interface and cross-browser compatibility, content on the SAMS platform is easily accessible
        and consistent across different web browsers and devices.</p>
      <h3 class="about-title">Robust, secure and private</h3>
      <p class="about-desc">Committed to safeguarding data security and user privacy, security controls are constantly
        being updated and implemented in SAMS development processes and software to protect against unauthorised access,
        data loss and misuse.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->


  <!-- FAQs -->
  <section class="faq" id="faq">
    <div class="faq-container">

      <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions
        <hr>
        <hr>
      </h1>

      <div class="qna-container">
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">What is the function of the attendance management system?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              An attendance management system is a software solution that helps class teachers mark and administrators
              track student attendance for an entire academic year.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">Who benefits from using an attendance management system?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              All the stakeholders of the institutions, which includes the class teachers, parents, admins, and the
              students themselves, can see the daily and overall attendance of the students using the attendance
              management system.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">Can teachers mark attendance if the students are not on SAMS?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              Yes, as long as the student details have been added to the SAMS portal by the admin, their attendance can
              be marked regardless of whether the student has signed up on the SAMS platform or not.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">Can teachers make changes to the attendance once it has been recorded?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              Yes, the online attendance system allows class teachers to edit or update attendance within the timeframe
              of the academic year set by the institution admin. This can help rectify any errors.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">How can teachers’ workload be reduced using SAMS portal?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              SAMS reduces teachers’ workload by automating the process of recording attendance. Moreover, teachers do
              not need to calculate attendance percentages manually as the system provides a detailed report which can
              help take important decisions.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="qna-item">
          <header class="qna-header">
            <h3 class="qna-item-title">Is SAMS complicated?</h3>
            <i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i>
          </header>
          <div class="qna-content">
            <p class="qna-desc">
              It depends on your skills. SAMS is very powerful, and with power comes complexity. It is intended to be
              easy as possible for teachers, students and administrators to use, for technicians to install, and for
              administrators to manage, however, there are a lot of options and settings and there is still some
              learning curve. Getting started is easy if you're not afraid to explore on your own.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <footer class="footer">
      <p class="copy-text">&copy; copyright 2023 SAMS - Students Attendance Management System | All rights reserved</p>
    </footer>
  </section>
  <!-- FAQs -->

  <script src="/javascripts/home.js"></script>
</body>

</html>